    <subfield code="a">This letter is concerned with domestic matters. Deborah Weston says about Mary [Gray Chapman]&apos;s condition: &quot;I call her very poorly.&quot; She describes Anne [Chapman]&apos;s gowns and appearance. Anne Chapman &quot;longs to get home to Weymouth, ...She has bought Hawthorne&apos;s new book to delect herself with tomorrow.&quot; [The book mentioned is Nathaniel Hawthorne&apos;s &quot;The Marble Faun,&quot; published in 1860.]</subfield>
